(323, 13, '2025-08-15 15:39:17', '2025-08-15 15:39:17', 'Justyn! I\'m so here for story time! 🔥\nI\'m totally voting for option #2 (the GPS disaster road trip) because that sounds like peak Alex energy - \"navigating by vibes\" is literally how they approach everything in life and somehow it always works out perfectly! 😂\nI\'ve been trying to decide on my story too and I think I\'m going with the time Alex convinced our entire dorm floor to have a \"fancy dinner party\" in the communal kitchen, complete with tablecloths made from bedsheets and \"gourmet\" ramen noodles. They turned the most basic college meal into this whole elegant experience and we all felt like we were dining at a five-star restaurant. Classic Alex move!\nAlso YES to guitar accompaniment! Nothing says \"meaningful bonfire vibes\" like some gentle strumming in the background. Just maybe avoid anything too sad because you KNOW Alex is going to get emotional anyway (in the best way) 🎸✨\nCan\'t wait to ugly cry around the fire with all of you! 💕', '', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', '323', '', '', '2025-08-15 15:39:17', '2025-08-15 15:39:17', '', 258, '/forums/reply/323/', 1, 'reply', '', 0),
(324, 19, '2025-08-15 15:41:42', '2025-08-15 15:41:42', 'OMG you guys are making me emotional already and we haven\'t even started! 😭💕\n\nJustyn, I\'m team #2 as well! The \"navigating by vibes\" story is SO Alex - they probably turned getting lost into the most fun adventure ever. And Agnes, the fancy dorm dinner party story is PERFECT! I remember Alex telling me about that - they said you all felt like royalty eating ramen with plastic forks 👑\n\nMy story contribution: Remember when Alex dragged me to that \"beginner-friendly\" salsa class and we spent the entire first session just trying to figure out which foot goes where? By the end, we had invented our own dance style that was definitely NOT salsa, but Alex was so proud of our \"creative interpretation\" that they convinced the instructor to let us demonstrate it to the class! Pure chaos, pure Alex energy.\n\nJustyn, I\'m bringing my portable speaker too, so we can have some ambient music for the stories if you want backup for your guitar! Maybe some soft acoustic stuff to set the mood? 🎵\nFair warning: I\'m definitely going to ugly cry during at least three of these stories. Someone please bring tissues! 🥺✨', '', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', '324', '', '', '2025-08-15 15:41:42', '2025-08-15 15:41:42', '', 258, '/forums/reply/324/', 2, 'reply', '', 0),
(325, 1, '2025-08-15 15:44:08', '2025-08-15 15:44:08', 'Dallas, you are officially my new favorite person! 🙌\n\nThank you for stepping up as our grill master – I was literally lying awake last night panicking about the food coordination, so you just saved my sanity! Your menu sounds absolutely perfect, and I\'m genuinely impressed that you\'re covering the veggie options too (Maya will be SO happy about those veggie burgers!).\n\nI\'m claiming buns and condiments duty – I\'ll bring:\n\n* All the burger buns (regular, whole wheat, and some fancy brioche ones because why not?)\n* Hot dog buns\n* The full condiment arsenal: ketchup, mustard, mayo, BBQ sauce, that fancy sriracha aioli everyone loves\n* Pickles, onions, lettuce, tomatoes – basically a whole burger bar setup\n\nI\'m also thinking we need some sides to go with your grilling masterpiece, so I\'m volunteering to coordinate a potato salad and maybe a pasta salad situation.\n\nQuestion though: Should someone bring a cooler specifically for keeping your meat cold until grill time? I can handle that too if needed!\n\nAnd LOL at judging our burger-flipping technique – I promise to stay FAR away from your grill and just appreciate your work from a safe distance with a drink in hand. That\'s probably better for everyone involved! 😂\n\nThis is going to be AMAZING. Alex is going to flip when they see this spread!', '', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', '325', '', '', '2025-08-15 15:44:26', '2025-08-15 15:44:26', '', 254, '/forums/reply/325/', 1, 'reply', '', 0),
