(327, 5, '2025-08-15 15:47:00', '2025-08-15 15:47:00', 'Sofia, Sofia, Sofia... 🤦‍♂️\n\nI respect the confidence, I really do. But you\'re about to learn the difference between catching dance props and catching a frisbee when there\'s a 15 mph ocean breeze and sand getting in your eyes!\n\nI\'ve been throwing perfect spirals since I was 12, and my hand-eye coordination has been honed by years of flipping burgers without dropping a single patty. You think those pirouettes are going to help you when I send a frisbee sailing right past your victory dance moves?\n\nHere\'s my counter-challenge: When (not if) I win this tournament, you have to let me teach YOU some proper throwing technique. And yes, there will be a step-by-step breakdown just like one of my grilling tutorials 😂\n\nBring those glow sticks though - you\'re gonna need something to light up the beach when you\'re picking yourself up off the sand! 🥏💪\n\nGame on, dance floor queen! 👑', '', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', '327', '', '', '2025-08-15 15:47:00', '2025-08-15 15:47:00', '', 220, '/forums/reply/327/', 2, 'reply', '', 0),
(328, 18, '2025-08-15 15:49:01', '2025-08-15 15:49:01', '<em>grabs popcorn and camera</em> 🍿📸\n\nThis is getting GOOD! I\'m just here for the entertainment value, honestly. Dallas talking about \"perfect spirals\" while Sofia\'s planning victory dances... meanwhile, I\'ll be the one capturing every spectacular wipeout in glorious high-definition!\n\nMy strategy is simple: stay back, document everything, and swoop in during the finals when everyone else is exhausted from all this trash talk energy 😎\n\nFair warning though - I\'ve got some secret frisbee skills from all those hiking trips where we had to entertain ourselves during lunch breaks. Alex can vouch for my surprisingly decent backhand throw!\n\nBut mostly I\'m just excited to get some action shots of Sofia attempting to catch a frisbee while doing a pirouette, and Dallas realizing that grilling skills don\'t automatically translate to beach sports 📷\n\nMay the best trash talker win! (And may I get some Instagram-worthy shots in the process) ✨', '', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', '328', '', '', '2025-08-15 15:49:01', '2025-08-15 15:49:01', '', 220, '/forums/reply/328/', 3, 'reply', '', 0),
(329, 1, '2025-08-15 15:49:42', '2025-08-15 15:49:42', 'Agnes, I\'ve got you covered! 🚗✨\n\nI\'m driving from downtown too and have plenty of room in my SUV - consider yourself officially my co-pilot! And honestly, homemade cookies as payment? That\'s the best deal I\'ve heard all week!\n\nI was actually planning to leave around 12:30 PM to get there with plenty of time before the welcome drinks at 2:00. Does that timing work for you? We can grab coffee on the way if we\'re feeling fancy!\n\nFor everyone else coordinating rides: I still have 2 more seats available in my car if anyone else needs a lift from the downtown area! I\'m the type of driver who keeps snacks, phone chargers, and definitely won\'t judge your music choices (though I draw the line at death metal at 8 AM 😂).\n\nAgnes, I\'m absolutely here for pre-party karaoke! Fair warning though - I have zero shame when it comes to belting out early 2000s pop hits, so prepare yourself for some truly questionable Britney Spears impressions. 🎤\n\nThis carpool coordination is such a great idea! Not only are we being eco-friendly, but road trip bonding time before we even get to the beach? Yes please!\n\nJust DM me your address and we\'ll figure out the pickup logistics. This is going to be so fun! 🎉', '', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', '329', '', '', '2025-08-15 15:49:42', '2025-08-15 15:49:42', '', 261, '/forums/reply/329/', 1, 'reply', '', 0),
(330, 13, '2025-08-15 15:50:54', '2025-08-15 15:50:54', 'Oh you guys are SO going down! 😤\n\nAnd by \"going down\" I mean you\'ll probably trip over me because I\'ll definitely be diving dramatically for frisbees that are nowhere near me! My strategy is pure chaos - if I can\'t catch the frisbee properly, I\'ll at least confuse everyone else with my interpretive diving techniques 🤸‍♀️\n\nDallas, your \"perfect spirals\" won\'t help when I\'m running in completely random directions! Sofia, your dance moves are no match for my signature move: the \"Agnes Flail\" (patent pending). And Marcus, good luck getting clear shots when I\'m creating a one-person dust storm on the beach!\n\nPlus I\'ve got secret weapons: I\'m bringing extra sunscreen for my teammates (team bonding!) AND I\'ve been practicing my celebratory whooping sounds. You\'ll hear me cheering from three beaches away!\n\nFair warning: I may not be good at frisbee, but I\'m EXCELLENT at making everyone laugh when they mess up. Psychological warfare at its finest! 😂🥏\n\nPrepare yourselves for the most enthusiastic mediocre frisbee playing you\'ve ever witnessed!', '', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', '330', '', '', '2025-08-15 15:50:54', '2025-08-15 15:50:54', '', 220, '/forums/reply/330/', 4, 'reply', '', 0),
(331, 1, '2025-08-15 15:51:31', '2025-08-15 15:51:31', 'Marcus, you are a LIFESAVER! 📸✨\n\nI was honestly starting to stress about how we were going to get good photos with everyone\'s phones and questionable selfie skills, so having an actual photography expert step up is amazing! Consider me your enthusiastic assistant director - I\'m 100% here for being bossed around if it means we get incredible shots!\n\nI love all your pose ideas, especially the walking toward camera one - that\'s going to look so natural and fun! And yes to the jumping shot! I don\'t care if it\'s cliché, Alex is going to absolutely lose it (in the best way) when they see all of us mid-air looking ridiculous.\n\nCan I make one tiny request? Could we also do a few shots during the bonfire time? I know the lighting will be totally different, but there\'s something so magical about that warm fire glow that would be perfect for capturing the cozy storytelling moments. Plus Alex\'s face when we surprise them with all the birthday shenanigans!\n\nI\'m also volunteering to be your photo assistant throughout the day - someone needs to wrangle people for the candid shots and make sure everyone\'s aware when you\'re trying to capture those perfect unposed moments. I\'m excellent at distracting people so they look natural! 😂\n\nThank you for thinking of individual friend group shots too! This party is going to be so well documented, and Alex is going to have the most incredible photo memories.\n\nYou\'re the best for organizing this! 📷💕', '', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', '331', '', '', '2025-08-15 15:51:31', '2025-08-15 15:51:31', '', 240, '/forums/reply/331/', 1, 'reply', '', 0),
